  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>garlic</strong>,</p><p>Chop the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in half lengthways and wash to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Add the<strong> whites </strong>of the<strong> sliced leek </strong>(save the greens for later!) with the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>and a pinch of a <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1640105140824-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1640105140824-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1640105140824-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1640105140824-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1640105140824-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge and open the packet to let it breathe before cooking</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 8-10 min or until fork-tender, then drain in a sieve and set aside, reserving the pot for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1640105185038-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1640105185038-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1640105185038-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1640105185038-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1640105185038-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, transfer everything from the pan to a plate and set aside for later</p><p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken breast portions</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1640105194493-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1640105194493-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1640105194493-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
