            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat and add a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> remaining leek </strong>with the <strong>spring greens</strong>,<strong> chopped green beans </strong>and<strong> </strong>a splash of<strong> water </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p><p>Once tender, add the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong> with a large splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and crush the potatoes gently with a potato masher – this is your <strong>crushed potato colcannon</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
